**THE NEXT NFT BOOM STARTS ON TELEGRAM. TON MAY BECOME THE WORLD‚ÄôS MAIN CHAIN

Our guest today: Jason Falovitch. –°reator of the market mint
**
One of the early movers behind the 2021 NFT boom ‚Äî and now a key figure shaping Web3 inside Telegram. I already shared a bit about who he is right here Now let‚Äôs talk about what he‚Äôs actually building ‚Äî and where it‚Äôs all headed.

üßê `Garlic:` **People call you an investor, a visionary, a media builder inside Telegram. But how would you define your own role in this ecosystem?**

üòâ `Jason:` I just see where things are heading and try to help shape it from the inside. I‚Äôve been fortunate to be early on a few things, but really, I‚Äôm just focused on building. I care about the culture, the tech, and how we bring it all together in a way that actually resonates on Telegram.

üßê `Garlic`: **Do you think Telegram could experience an NFT boom comparable to what we saw in 2021?**

üòâ `Jason: `Not just comparable, bigger. I started the NFT movement with Mark Cuban in 2021. That wave was about hype and headlines. Telegram‚Äôs will be about utility and distribution. We‚Äôre not relying on speculation here. Gifts, stickers, usernames ‚Äî this is behavior people already love. All we‚Äôre doing is adding ownership.

üßê `Garlic: `**What do you see as the key priorities for developing Web3 functionality inside Telegram and what needs to happen to make it truly mainstream?**

üòâ `Jason: `Make it invisible. That is the secret sauce. No seed phrases, no extra apps, no friction. Telegram already is mainstream. Web3 just needs to disappear into the product. @wallet was the first big unlock. Gifts, stickers, usernames, and creator tools are next. All native, all seamless.

üßê `Garlic: `**NFT gifts are one of the core focuses of your channel. Do you genuinely believe this format has a future?**

üòâ `Jason: `Absolutely. Gifts are already native to Telegram. People use them to communicate and flex. Turning those into NFTs just adds value and scarcity. Stickers follow the same logic. We‚Äôre not trying to invent behavior. We‚Äôre just making it ownable. That is the future.

üßê `Garlic:` **The project Mint is getting a lot of attention in the community. Is this a new marketplace? Can you give us even a hint of what to expect?**

üòâ `Jason:` Mint isn‚Äôt just a marketplace. It is a platform for moments. Think drops, collectibles, identity, all rooted in Telegram‚Äôs UX. It is about building emotional connection and flex culture inside chats. That is all I‚Äôll say for now.

üßê `Garlic: `**How do you see the future of TON and Telegram over the next 3 to 5 years?**

üòâ `Jason:` Telegram will become the front page of crypto. TON will be the most used chain in the world because it is embedded directly in the app that already has over a billion users. In five years, everything from sending money to minting NFTs will just feel like chat.

üßê `Garlic:`** You‚Äôre known for investing in high-risk NFTs, including Bored Ape. Would you say you‚Äôre someone who enjoys risk or is every move part of a calculated strategy?**

üòâ `Jason:` It is never about the risk, it is about conviction. I saw the cultural momentum behind Bored Ape before it broke out. Same with Telegram. When I move, it is because I believe the upside is worth the noise.

üßê `Garlic: `**If you could leave one short message for the TON and Telegram community, what would it be?**

üòâ `Jason: `You‚Äôre early, but that won‚Äôt last. Own the assets, build the culture, and stay loud inside Telegram. This window closes fast.

üßê `Garlic:`** Let‚Äôs say you‚Äôre sitting across the table from Pavel Durov. What‚Äôs the one question you‚Äôd ask him about Telegram or TON?**

üòâ `Jason:` What would it take to make digital identity and ownership fully native to Telegram? Because once that is live, everything else unlocks.
